/-
Formalization of the Frobenius Orientation Theorem and the Irreducibility Criterion.

This module contains the formal statements and proofs (delegated to the ATP) of:
1. `frobenius_orientation`: The main theorem stating that the Frobenius automorphism on the roots of f(x) = x^3 - qx - q is determined by the cubic character of N mod q.
2. `irreducibility_criterion`: A criterion for the irreducibility of f(x) mod N based on the cubic character of N mod q.
3. `frobenius_action_on_roots`: A helper lemma describing the action of the Frobenius on the roots in the residue field of the cyclotomic extension.

The formalization follows the structure of the provided LaTeX document, utilizing the "Dream Theorem" and transfer arguments.
-/

